cff-version: 1.2.0
message: If you use this work, please cite it using the metadata below.
type: dataset
title: QUIC Server and Client Performance Evaluation Across Multiple Implementations
abstract: This dataset documents an experiment evaluating the performance of several
  QUIC server and client implementations under varying network conditions. The methodology
  involved automated setup of nodes, installation of software packages, compilation
  of QUIC libraries, and execution of client-server transfer tests with controlled
  bandwidth limits and file sizes.  Evaluation scripts analyzed per-run logs to determine
  goodput and generate visualizations summarizing the relationship between bandwidth
  limitations and achieved throughput across different implementations. Archive contents
  include build scripts, configuration files, evaluation outputs, and per-run log
  data.
